Today I went to this place for dinner.  I ordered the crackling chicken combination,with veggie fried rice and vegetable salad.   I felt the meal was overpriced as I was,expecting a salad, and not just a slice of tomato  and five pieces of lettuce. The chicken I could tell had been fried over and being white meat it became overdone and chewy.  The presentation was poor as all the food  was piled up on one plate and after asking for a small plate to remove the veggies I saw that the water from it had settled on the bottom of the plate.  Having gotten no napkin  which I thought was an oversight i had to remove the one from the bread basket  to mop up the liquid. The meal came with no sauce and when I asked for the pepper oil I was given a mushy pepper blend.  From the start I could tell my experience was gonna be off when the bread basket came with the bread which had been out was leathery and cold. When I was asked if I wanted to order drink and declined I was not offered the usual water and again I had to ask.  This again came without ice in it or the few pieces of lemon usually offered and only while I started to choke  on the rough fibres of the chicken breast.
